1
00:00:35,333 --> 00:00:36,250
[grunts]

2
00:00:36,333 --> 00:00:37,791
Those guys!

3
00:00:37,875 --> 00:00:39,708
Do they have no manners?

4
00:00:39,791 --> 00:00:42,166
How many times
do I have to tell them?

5
00:00:42,250 --> 00:00:43,666
[door opens]

6
00:00:43,750 --> 00:00:45,250
Which one of you just
came through the front door?

7
00:00:45,333 --> 00:00:47,291
Come on, fess up.

8
00:00:47,375 --> 00:00:49,458
If I've told you once
I've told you a thousand times,

9
00:00:49,541 --> 00:00:51,583
you are not to slam
any doors in this house!

10
00:00:51,666 --> 00:00:53,958
Also, you both smell
like a barn.

11
00:00:54,041 --> 00:00:56,125
For the love of God,
go take a damn bath!

12
00:00:56,208 --> 00:00:57,250
You're distracting me.

13
00:00:57,333 --> 00:00:59,041
I can't work
in these conditions!

14
00:01:00,041 --> 00:01:02,041
Now, both of you apologize.

15
00:01:02,125 --> 00:01:04,625
Look in Tsurumi's eyes
and say you're sorry.

16
00:01:09,125 --> 00:01:11,833
Isn't he great?
I made him last night.

17
00:01:11,916 --> 00:01:14,000
Well, I think you two
have something to say!

18
00:01:14,083 --> 00:01:15,416
Do your job.

19
00:01:15,500 --> 00:01:17,458
Don't keep wasting time
on dumb stuff like that.

20
00:01:17,541 --> 00:01:21,666
I won't hear this!
He deserves an apology!

21
00:01:21,750 --> 00:01:25,041
Tsurumi?! Look what you did!

22
00:02:56,083 --> 00:02:57,916
[EDOGAI]
They're finally finished.

23
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:01,250
There have never been
more perfect fake skins.

24
00:03:01,333 --> 00:03:03,708
These six
are only the beginning.

25
00:03:03,791 --> 00:03:06,666
Tsurumi is going to be
so happy with me!

26
00:03:06,750 --> 00:03:09,083
He'll pat me on the head
and tell me I did good.

27
00:03:09,166 --> 00:03:10,416
[glass shatters]

28
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:13,416
What the hell was that?
That you, Maeyama?

29
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:16,500
How many times
do I have to tell you to...

30
00:03:16,583 --> 00:03:18,250
M...

31
00:03:18,333 --> 00:03:19,458
Maeyama?

32
00:03:26,458 --> 00:03:29,375
Who is that man? Why's he here?

33
00:03:29,458 --> 00:03:31,250
Did he come to steal the skins?

34
00:03:33,625 --> 00:03:35,041
[train horn blowing]

35
00:03:39,541 --> 00:03:40,875
[BOY]
Look, the smoke's splitting

36
00:03:40,958 --> 00:03:42,416
when it comes out
of the smokestack.

37
00:03:42,500 --> 00:03:44,000
Somebody's gonna die
in the mines.

38
00:03:44,083 --> 00:03:45,166
You stop that!

39
00:03:46,208 --> 00:03:48,791
Well, this is great.
I forgot my wallet.

40
00:03:51,291 --> 00:03:53,500
[SUGIMOTO]
Hey, did you see that guy?

41
00:03:53,583 --> 00:03:55,375
Wasn't he one
of Tsurumi's troops?

42
00:03:55,458 --> 00:03:58,291
Huh. I don't know for sure,
but he could be.

43
00:03:58,375 --> 00:04:00,041
Wonder if he heard the rumors

44
00:04:00,125 --> 00:04:02,583
about a house
full of tattooed skins, too.

45
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,083
Come on, let's follow him.

46
00:04:05,166 --> 00:04:07,041
Wait, what about
the others, though,

47
00:04:07,125 --> 00:04:08,375
over there?

48
00:04:08,458 --> 00:04:10,666
They've been questioning
some of the locals.

49
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:13,125
[SUGIMOTO]
No time, they're okay. Let's go.

50
00:04:14,791 --> 00:04:16,083
[EDOGAI panting]

51
00:04:16,166 --> 00:04:18,250
I've got to get out of here.

52
00:04:18,333 --> 00:04:21,000
Except, the only real exit
is the front door.

53
00:04:21,083 --> 00:04:22,208
What do I do?

54
00:04:22,291 --> 00:04:24,208
-[cat meows]
-Huh?

55
00:04:24,291 --> 00:04:26,541
Now is not the time!

56
00:04:33,166 --> 00:04:35,083
[OGATA]
Tsukishima takes long baths.

57
00:04:35,166 --> 00:04:36,708
He won't be back for a while.

58
00:04:41,125 --> 00:04:43,041
That means that I should
have plenty of time

59
00:04:43,125 --> 00:04:46,166
to make the taxidermist spill
whatever they've been planning.

60
00:04:47,916 --> 00:04:48,875
[door creaks]

61
00:04:48,958 --> 00:04:51,291
♪

62
00:04:57,083 --> 00:04:58,958
[MAN]
Excuse me, sir.

63
00:04:59,041 --> 00:05:01,250
-Hmm?
-Uh, this'll sound strange,

64
00:05:01,333 --> 00:05:03,333
but a white bear
ran that way just now.

65
00:05:03,416 --> 00:05:06,125
Think of that.
Make sure to hydrate, okay, sir?

66
00:05:06,208 --> 00:05:07,708
Uh...

67
00:05:07,791 --> 00:05:09,041
[door creaks]

68
00:05:10,375 --> 00:05:11,291
Huh?

69
00:05:13,708 --> 00:05:15,416
What the hell is this?

70
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:18,000
[gasps]

71
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:21,625
How sweet.

72
00:05:21,708 --> 00:05:24,833
Looks like the taxidermist kid's
in love with Lieutenant Tsurumi.

73
00:05:31,208 --> 00:05:33,083
If these are
what I think they are...

74
00:05:34,833 --> 00:05:37,375
It gives Tsurumi far too great
of an advantage.

75
00:05:39,708 --> 00:05:40,625
[gasps]

76
00:05:41,625 --> 00:05:43,291
Shit. He got away.

77
00:05:47,708 --> 00:05:48,791
-[grunts]
-[groans]

78
00:05:56,666 --> 00:06:01,250
You bastard!
You'll pay for Maeyama.

79
00:06:01,333 --> 00:06:04,416
How could you kill
your former comrade? Huh?

80
00:06:06,083 --> 00:06:08,125
[OGATA] Both of you are working
against the government.

81
00:06:08,208 --> 00:06:10,250
You're HQ's little pet.

82
00:06:10,333 --> 00:06:13,000
I know exactly
what you're doing.

83
00:06:13,083 --> 00:06:14,958
You're offering rebels
up to the government

84
00:06:15,041 --> 00:06:17,625
just to get yourself promoted.

85
00:06:17,708 --> 00:06:19,666
Your father led
the Seventh Division,

86
00:06:19,750 --> 00:06:22,541
and you're willing to sell out
your friends to surpass him.

87
00:06:22,625 --> 00:06:25,166
"Comrades and friends,
a great brotherhood."

88
00:06:25,250 --> 00:06:27,458
You're a master
at using cheesy lines

89
00:06:27,541 --> 00:06:29,416
to trick stupid young men.

90
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:31,333
Aren't you, Tsurumi?

91
00:06:34,458 --> 00:06:35,708
[HAJIME]
How many left?

92
00:06:36,791 --> 00:06:38,625
Edogai, you still alive?

93
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:44,916
[gasps]

94
00:06:47,625 --> 00:06:49,375
Uh, this'll sound strange,

95
00:06:49,458 --> 00:06:52,250
but a white bear
ran that way just now.

96
00:06:52,333 --> 00:06:53,375
He didn't.

97
00:06:53,458 --> 00:06:55,583
[EDOGAI panting]

98
00:07:00,416 --> 00:07:03,250
I've gotta get these to Tsurumi.

99
00:07:08,916 --> 00:07:11,125
So, he went after Edogai.

100
00:07:11,208 --> 00:07:13,583
I need to find him
before Tsukishima does.

101
00:07:13,666 --> 00:07:14,833
[door opens and closes]

102
00:07:14,916 --> 00:07:16,375
We just gonna ignore
that soldier

103
00:07:16,458 --> 00:07:18,458
we passed on the way in?

104
00:07:18,541 --> 00:07:20,291
I wanna check this place out.

105
00:07:20,375 --> 00:07:22,875
[OGATA]
Immortal Sugimoto.

106
00:07:22,958 --> 00:07:25,958
Excellent, one more thing
to worry about.

107
00:07:26,041 --> 00:07:28,416
Hey, look at this.
There's a body here.

108
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:31,625
Suspicious, for sure.
This might be the place.

109
00:07:34,291 --> 00:07:36,916
[SHIRAISHI]
Gah! What the hell is this?

110
00:07:38,208 --> 00:07:39,208
[gasps]

111
00:07:39,291 --> 00:07:40,541
Shh.

112
00:07:40,625 --> 00:07:41,833
[shudders]

113
00:07:41,916 --> 00:07:44,583
You're Yoshitake Shiraishi,
aren't you?

114
00:07:44,666 --> 00:07:47,333
Hijikata told me
all about you.

115
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:51,708
Maybe I should make them
stop Tsukishima for me.

116
00:07:53,125 --> 00:07:55,041
-[SHIRAISHI] Sugimoto!
-Hmm?

117
00:07:55,125 --> 00:07:56,666
Look at this thing.

118
00:07:56,750 --> 00:07:58,375
Brace yourself, this is weird,

119
00:07:58,458 --> 00:08:01,750
but I think Lieutenant Tsurumi
was having fake skins made here.

120
00:08:01,833 --> 00:08:03,500
And that soldier who ran out,

121
00:08:03,583 --> 00:08:05,875
I bet you anything
he was stealing them.

122
00:08:05,958 --> 00:08:08,000
We need to go
after him right now.

123
00:08:08,083 --> 00:08:10,291
[EDOGAI panting]

124
00:08:11,791 --> 00:08:13,791
Tsurumi. I'm coming.

125
00:08:13,875 --> 00:08:15,333
[kids laughing]

126
00:08:16,958 --> 00:08:18,250
You kids see a white bear?

127
00:08:18,333 --> 00:08:19,833
Mm-mmm.

128
00:08:19,916 --> 00:08:23,333
♪

129
00:08:26,583 --> 00:08:27,791
[inaudible]

130
00:08:37,500 --> 00:08:40,958
Tsurumi. Tsurumi.
Tsurumi. Tsurumi. Ah!

131
00:08:42,208 --> 00:08:44,041
[OGATA]
Hey, Edogai.

132
00:08:44,125 --> 00:08:45,250
Huh?

133
00:08:46,208 --> 00:08:48,541
Your luck ran out
when you met the Grim Reaper

134
00:08:48,625 --> 00:08:50,208
known as Lieutenant Tsurumi.

135
00:08:50,291 --> 00:08:51,916
[panting]

136
00:08:54,041 --> 00:08:55,416
-[yells]
-Huh?

137
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:56,875
Get in here, Edogai!

138
00:08:59,750 --> 00:09:00,666
There!

139
00:09:03,083 --> 00:09:04,416
Tsukishima.

140
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:06,375
I think we should use
the tunnels to lose them.

141
00:09:06,458 --> 00:09:08,041
They all loop back
on each other,

142
00:09:08,125 --> 00:09:10,500
and there are tons
of different ways out.

143
00:09:10,583 --> 00:09:12,875
I'm getting these fake skins
I made to Tsurumi

144
00:09:12,958 --> 00:09:14,291
no matter what.

145
00:09:14,375 --> 00:09:16,708
He's going to be so proud
of my beautiful work.

146
00:09:16,791 --> 00:09:20,125
I want him to pat me on the head
and give me great big kiss.

147
00:09:20,208 --> 00:09:22,208
Oh, my sweet Tsurumi!

148
00:09:22,291 --> 00:09:23,208
Huh!

149
00:09:26,291 --> 00:09:27,958
Immortal Sugimoto?

150
00:09:28,041 --> 00:09:30,041
I guess that means
he must've heard the rumors

151
00:09:30,125 --> 00:09:31,708
about the tattooed skins.

152
00:09:33,500 --> 00:09:35,791
Hey, we can't let
these guys get away.

153
00:09:35,875 --> 00:09:38,208
If those fake skins get out
there and start circulating,

154
00:09:38,291 --> 00:09:40,166
there's gonna be total chaos.

155
00:09:44,208 --> 00:09:45,625
[yelling]

156
00:09:48,291 --> 00:09:50,833
-[groans]
-Huh?

157
00:09:53,958 --> 00:09:54,958
[shouts]

158
00:09:56,583 --> 00:09:57,875
Leave me alone!

159
00:10:00,666 --> 00:10:02,000
Oh, dammit.

160
00:10:03,666 --> 00:10:05,625
Not good.
They're gonna catch up now.

161
00:10:08,833 --> 00:10:10,750
[grunting]

162
00:10:13,458 --> 00:10:15,791
[yelling] Give me those skins,
you freak!

163
00:10:15,875 --> 00:10:17,083
Get lost!

164
00:10:19,791 --> 00:10:20,916
Shiraishi, watch out!

165
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:23,875
My pants are about to split!

166
00:10:23,958 --> 00:10:24,875
[fabric ripping]

167
00:10:26,416 --> 00:10:28,166
[yelling]

168
00:10:42,583 --> 00:10:44,333
[EDOGAI]
He's the guy who killed Maeyama.

169
00:10:44,416 --> 00:10:45,666
[HAJIME]
That's Ogata.

170
00:10:45,750 --> 00:10:47,958
Keep your head down
or he'll blow it off.

171
00:10:48,041 --> 00:10:50,166
Hey! Stop!
Too dangerous!

172
00:10:50,250 --> 00:10:53,041
We lit the 'mite,
so you have to stop now.

173
00:10:53,125 --> 00:10:54,625
You'll get caught
in the explosion!

174
00:10:54,708 --> 00:10:55,708
No.

175
00:10:57,958 --> 00:11:00,375
-What were they yelling?
-Don't know.

176
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:04,583
[screams]

177
00:11:04,666 --> 00:11:07,333
That must've been dynamite,
and it was close.

178
00:11:07,416 --> 00:11:08,916
It was so scary.

179
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:12,375
But, look,
now they can't follow us.

180
00:11:12,458 --> 00:11:15,833
Let's escape out
the other side of the mountain.

181
00:11:15,916 --> 00:11:18,000
[OGATA grunting]
Damn it.

182
00:11:18,083 --> 00:11:20,625
Hey, do you guys
smell something?

183
00:11:20,708 --> 00:11:22,833
Yeah, it kind of smells
like burning metal.

184
00:11:22,916 --> 00:11:24,875
[sighs]
Oh!

185
00:11:28,375 --> 00:11:29,791
It's firedamp!

186
00:11:29,875 --> 00:11:32,500
I think the blast
must have hit a pocket of gas.

187
00:11:32,583 --> 00:11:34,583
Run! It's gonna blow!

188
00:11:45,916 --> 00:11:47,208
[coughing]

189
00:11:47,291 --> 00:11:48,541
[groans]

190
00:11:48,625 --> 00:11:50,833
Oh, great.
Things are just blowing up now?

191
00:11:50,916 --> 00:11:52,541
I don't wanna find out.
Come on.

192
00:11:52,625 --> 00:11:54,791
[wind gushing]

193
00:11:54,875 --> 00:11:56,083
What the...

194
00:11:56,166 --> 00:11:57,333
What is this wind?

195
00:11:58,708 --> 00:12:00,833
[groaning]

196
00:12:00,916 --> 00:12:02,791
It's a returner!

197
00:12:02,875 --> 00:12:04,666
There might be
another bigger blast!

198
00:12:04,750 --> 00:12:06,458
Get out of here, now!

199
00:12:06,541 --> 00:12:08,208
[groaning]

200
00:12:08,291 --> 00:12:09,958
[explosion]

201
00:12:14,958 --> 00:12:16,500
[explosion]

202
00:12:16,583 --> 00:12:18,166
[birds cawing]

203
00:12:18,250 --> 00:12:20,333
[VILLAGER]
Another gas explosion.

204
00:12:20,416 --> 00:12:22,875
That was the biggest one
we've had for a long while.

205
00:12:22,958 --> 00:12:24,625
Felt like it shook
the whole mountain.

206
00:12:24,708 --> 00:12:26,291
This is terrible.

207
00:12:29,666 --> 00:12:30,666
[HAJIME]
Edogai!

208
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:32,625
[coughing]

209
00:12:32,708 --> 00:12:35,208
Where are you? Edogai!

210
00:12:36,250 --> 00:12:37,583
[EDOGAI]
Tsukishima.

211
00:12:37,666 --> 00:12:39,916
[coughs]
I'm over here.

212
00:12:41,375 --> 00:12:44,083
There you are.
I'm gonna get you out.

213
00:12:44,166 --> 00:12:47,750
[EDOGAI] Tsukishima,
you need to run, now.

214
00:12:47,833 --> 00:12:50,708
[weakly] The only way to stop
the fire from spreading,

215
00:12:50,791 --> 00:12:53,166
is to cut off the air supply.

216
00:12:53,250 --> 00:12:56,250
So what they'll do is
seal all the exits,

217
00:12:56,333 --> 00:12:58,750
even if they know
there are still people inside.

218
00:12:58,833 --> 00:13:00,125
Then let's go.

219
00:13:00,208 --> 00:13:02,416
I can't. My leg.

220
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:04,958
[grunts]
It got crushed pretty bad.

221
00:13:06,916 --> 00:13:09,833
Take this to Tsurumi.

222
00:13:09,916 --> 00:13:12,000
[coughing]

223
00:13:12,083 --> 00:13:13,958
[gasping]
He was the first person

224
00:13:14,041 --> 00:13:16,291
to take me seriously.

225
00:13:16,375 --> 00:13:17,666
[coughing]

226
00:13:17,750 --> 00:13:19,625
This was what he wanted
from me in return.

227
00:13:19,708 --> 00:13:23,083
Please take care of them, okay?

228
00:13:23,166 --> 00:13:24,750
'Course.

229
00:13:24,833 --> 00:13:27,041
[EDOGAI] And there's
one more thing that I...

230
00:13:27,125 --> 00:13:29,250
There's something
I want you to tell him.

231
00:13:30,208 --> 00:13:32,791
What is it?
Quickly, Edogai!

232
00:13:32,875 --> 00:13:35,000
[rumbling]

233
00:13:35,083 --> 00:13:39,125
Shiraishi. Wake up, come on.

234
00:13:39,208 --> 00:13:41,125
Hey, idiot, wake up.

235
00:13:42,666 --> 00:13:44,291
[retching]

236
00:13:47,791 --> 00:13:51,208
Why am I so sleepy?
Is it the gas?

237
00:13:56,083 --> 00:13:59,958
Screw that.
I'm the Immortal Sugimoto!

238
00:14:00,041 --> 00:14:02,250
[MINERS clamoring]

239
00:14:15,875 --> 00:14:18,125
[OGATA coughing]

240
00:14:18,208 --> 00:14:21,500
I don't even know
where I'm going.

241
00:14:21,583 --> 00:14:22,583
[gasps]

242
00:14:26,375 --> 00:14:28,166
You there. Not that way.

243
00:14:28,250 --> 00:14:30,375
Follow me.
The air vent's over here.

244
00:14:32,583 --> 00:14:33,708
[grunting]

245
00:14:33,791 --> 00:14:36,500
[coughing]

246
00:14:36,583 --> 00:14:38,250
[groaning]

247
00:14:39,791 --> 00:14:41,166
[panting]

248
00:14:46,250 --> 00:14:47,708
[coughs]

249
00:14:47,791 --> 00:14:49,208
[groaning]

250
00:14:49,291 --> 00:14:51,458
You've got to be kidding me.

251
00:14:51,541 --> 00:14:52,541
[grunts]

252
00:14:56,750 --> 00:14:58,583
[yells]

253
00:14:58,666 --> 00:14:59,916
[thuds]

254
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,958
[grunting]

255
00:15:06,791 --> 00:15:09,125
Shiraishi, breathe!

256
00:15:09,208 --> 00:15:11,583
I can't have you up
and dying on me now.

257
00:15:11,666 --> 00:15:13,916
Shiraishi! Wake up!

258
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:16,666
[coughing]

259
00:15:16,750 --> 00:15:20,125
[SUGIMOTO]
Shit. Not here. Please.

260
00:15:23,166 --> 00:15:24,708
[thudding]

261
00:15:26,500 --> 00:15:28,208
[murmuring]

262
00:15:30,541 --> 00:15:32,416
Look at that!
Someone’s out!

263
00:15:32,500 --> 00:15:33,458
[gasping]

264
00:15:33,541 --> 00:15:35,000
[MINER 1]
How did he survive?

265
00:15:35,083 --> 00:15:38,458
[MINER 2] Wow. Incredible.
He saved two other people.

266
00:15:43,416 --> 00:15:44,958
Ah!

267
00:15:47,958 --> 00:15:50,375
Hey there, girl.
We meet again.

268
00:15:51,666 --> 00:15:53,250
[chuckles softly]

269
00:15:53,333 --> 00:15:54,666
Dick-sensei.

270
00:15:55,875 --> 00:15:58,333
[SUGIMOTO] The fish cake?
She's still got it?

271
00:16:04,541 --> 00:16:06,208
[pants]

272
00:16:06,291 --> 00:16:08,333
What are you doing here, anyway?

273
00:16:08,416 --> 00:16:10,541
I came to Yuubari with someone,

274
00:16:10,625 --> 00:16:12,541
but he seems
to have disappeared.

275
00:16:12,625 --> 00:16:14,125
I was searching.

276
00:16:14,208 --> 00:16:16,416
That's what I was doing
when I found you in that cart.

277
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:18,333
-Someone?
-Hmm.

278
00:16:19,375 --> 00:16:21,083
Hmm?

279
00:16:21,166 --> 00:16:24,416
Guess it's fine.
We'll take them with us.

280
00:16:24,500 --> 00:16:27,625
What the hell is going on?
You were with Tsurumi.

281
00:16:27,708 --> 00:16:29,458
Why are you with Ushiyama?

282
00:16:32,541 --> 00:16:34,083
So, as you can see,

283
00:16:34,166 --> 00:16:35,958
these six bodies
give us a good idea

284
00:16:36,041 --> 00:16:39,041
where the taxidermist got
the skins for the fakes.

285
00:16:39,125 --> 00:16:42,125
We know for a fact
that the taxidermist is dead.

286
00:16:42,208 --> 00:16:45,000
But Sergeant Tsukishima
is a tough soldier.

287
00:16:45,083 --> 00:16:48,000
Until they pull his dead body
out of those tunnels,

288
00:16:48,083 --> 00:16:50,583
we have to assume that there are
six counterfeit skins

289
00:16:50,666 --> 00:16:52,875
already in circulation
out there in the world.

290
00:16:54,666 --> 00:16:55,791
[meows]

291
00:17:01,708 --> 00:17:03,166
-[meows]
-Hmm?

292
00:17:03,250 --> 00:17:05,333
[HIJIKATA]
If anyone has any clever ideas,

293
00:17:05,416 --> 00:17:08,083
we need to find some way
to test this skin.

294
00:17:08,166 --> 00:17:10,875
He left it behind,
but who knows if it's real.

295
00:17:10,958 --> 00:17:12,333
[cat purring]

296
00:17:13,375 --> 00:17:14,208
[shudders]

297
00:17:14,291 --> 00:17:16,083
♪

298
00:17:21,250 --> 00:17:23,375
Thanks for
the unsolicited tip.

299
00:17:23,458 --> 00:17:25,041
Have we met before?

300
00:17:25,125 --> 00:17:26,500
Shit.

301
00:17:28,958 --> 00:17:31,083
What? Don't be silly. No way.

302
00:17:31,166 --> 00:17:33,166
This man is Toshizou Hijikata.

303
00:17:33,250 --> 00:17:35,041
Hijikata.

304
00:17:35,125 --> 00:17:36,375
[meows]

305
00:17:36,458 --> 00:17:39,208
It's been a long time,
Yoshitake Shiraishi.

306
00:17:39,291 --> 00:17:40,416
Why don't you go ahead

307
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:43,166
and introduce me
to your friend, here?

308
00:17:43,250 --> 00:17:45,125
[SHIRAISHI] You're playing
with fire, old man.

309
00:17:45,208 --> 00:17:47,416
I mean, what's the plan
if he finds out?

310
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:48,708
Will Sugimoto kill me

311
00:17:48,791 --> 00:17:50,500
if he knows
I've been passing them info?

312
00:17:50,583 --> 00:17:54,208
There's a question I've wanted
to ask if we ever met.

313
00:17:54,291 --> 00:17:55,791
About Nopperabo.

314
00:17:55,875 --> 00:17:58,625
There's something he must have
told you and nobody else.

315
00:17:58,708 --> 00:18:01,125
So, either he trusted you
to some degree,

316
00:18:01,208 --> 00:18:02,541
or you shared a common goal,

317
00:18:02,625 --> 00:18:04,583
but I'm not sure
which one it is.

318
00:18:04,666 --> 00:18:08,375
Did he propose that you
provide weapons to the Ainu

319
00:18:08,458 --> 00:18:11,000
and start a war of independence?

320
00:18:11,083 --> 00:18:13,541
Which then begs the question.

321
00:18:13,625 --> 00:18:14,958
Is he an Ainu?

322
00:18:15,041 --> 00:18:16,541
[gasps]

323
00:18:16,625 --> 00:18:20,208
My. So, you've already gotten
that far, then, have you?

324
00:18:20,291 --> 00:18:22,708
[SUGIMOTO] Yeah,
once in a while, I get lucky.

325
00:18:22,791 --> 00:18:25,125
Is your plan
to get one up on Nopperabo

326
00:18:25,208 --> 00:18:27,666
and rebuild
the Republic of Ezo?

327
00:18:27,750 --> 00:18:29,625
Toshizou Hijikata?

328
00:18:29,708 --> 00:18:30,750
My father is a--

329
00:18:30,833 --> 00:18:32,250
[HIJIKATA]
Do we work together,

330
00:18:32,333 --> 00:18:35,125
or do we kill each other
right here?

331
00:18:35,208 --> 00:18:36,625
Make your choice.

332
00:18:36,708 --> 00:18:38,125
Hmm.

333
00:18:39,458 --> 00:18:42,833
[OGATA] Hijikata just cut
that girl off when she spoke up.

334
00:18:42,916 --> 00:18:45,375
She said, "my father."

335
00:18:45,458 --> 00:18:48,958
So, is she Nopperabo's daughter?

336
00:18:49,041 --> 00:18:50,375
[rumbling]

337
00:18:52,291 --> 00:18:54,250
If you have any
of the tattooed skins

338
00:18:54,333 --> 00:18:56,250
we'd be happy
to buy them from you.

339
00:18:56,333 --> 00:18:59,458
[SHIRAISHI]
Shinpachi Nagakura is here, too?

340
00:18:59,541 --> 00:19:03,125
We're not going to burden you
by asking for your help.

341
00:19:03,208 --> 00:19:05,833
We're prepared to pay you
quite handsomely for the skins.

342
00:19:05,916 --> 00:19:09,041
Then you can go home,
find a wife, and live in peace.

343
00:19:09,125 --> 00:19:12,541
Or is that too boring a life
for a young man like yourself?

344
00:19:13,583 --> 00:19:15,500
First I've got
to meet Nopperabo.

345
00:19:15,583 --> 00:19:17,000
I need some answers.

346
00:19:17,083 --> 00:19:20,166
Until then, I can't have you
finding that gold.

347
00:19:20,250 --> 00:19:22,583
[rumbling]

348
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:32,000
What the hell is
with the rumbling?!

349
00:19:32,083 --> 00:19:33,708
[rumbling continues]

350
00:19:35,291 --> 00:19:37,583
[WOMAN] Can I get
you gentlemen anything?

351
00:19:38,875 --> 00:19:40,583
[SUGIMOTO]
Ienaga's alive?

352
00:19:40,666 --> 00:19:42,291
If I might make a suggestion,

353
00:19:42,375 --> 00:19:45,083
why not finish your business
over a hot meal?

354
00:19:45,166 --> 00:19:46,916
♪

355
00:20:03,416 --> 00:20:05,416
[IENAGA]
This is nanko stew.

356
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:08,250
It's a local dish made
in the Sorachi area.

357
00:20:08,333 --> 00:20:12,000
It's an offal stew.
Boiled intestines in miso.

358
00:20:12,083 --> 00:20:15,625
Hey, Ienaga. This meat's
totally safe to eat, right?

359
00:20:15,708 --> 00:20:16,916
Of course it is.

360
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:19,041
Nanko simply means
"horse intestine"

361
00:20:19,125 --> 00:20:20,583
in the local dialect.

362
00:20:20,666 --> 00:20:21,958
Horse, eh? Hmm.

363
00:20:22,041 --> 00:20:23,458
I don't get it.

364
00:20:23,541 --> 00:20:25,916
How do you guys all manage
to work together?

365
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:30,416
I mean, how do you trust a guy
who used to work for Tsurumi?

366
00:20:30,500 --> 00:20:33,875
It's like they say,
once a traitor always a traitor.

367
00:20:33,958 --> 00:20:37,500
Aw, Sugimoto,
you almost killed me, you know,

368
00:20:37,583 --> 00:20:40,125
but thankfully, I'm not the type
to hold a grudge.

369
00:20:40,208 --> 00:20:42,416
I won't lie, though,
it hurt me.

370
00:20:45,333 --> 00:20:47,375
No fighting
during lunch, now, okay?

371
00:20:49,458 --> 00:20:51,000
Our main priority at the moment

372
00:20:51,083 --> 00:20:53,791
has to be finding a way to tell
which ones are the fakes.

373
00:20:53,875 --> 00:20:56,875
♪

374
00:21:01,791 --> 00:21:04,000
Lieutenant. I've returned.

375
00:21:05,958 --> 00:21:08,000
The highest ambition
of an artist

376
00:21:08,083 --> 00:21:11,333
is to leave his work behind
for the world to enjoy.

377
00:21:11,416 --> 00:21:13,500
And if it's something
so extraordinary,

378
00:21:13,583 --> 00:21:14,750
it could change the world,

379
00:21:14,833 --> 00:21:16,916
who could ask
for more than that?

380
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:18,833
[sniffs]
Hmm!

381
00:21:18,916 --> 00:21:22,333
Edogai, sir. His last words
were a message for you.

382
00:21:22,416 --> 00:21:24,666
What is it?

383
00:21:24,750 --> 00:21:27,750
[EDOGAI]
Iron. Just tell him, "iron."

384
00:21:27,833 --> 00:21:28,708
"Iron"?

385
00:21:28,791 --> 00:21:30,541
Tsurumi's so clever.

386
00:21:30,625 --> 00:21:33,625
I know he'll be able
to figure it out just from that.

387
00:21:37,958 --> 00:21:41,083
Well done. Go on
and get some rest, Tsukishima.

388
00:21:41,166 --> 00:21:42,208
Sir.

389
00:21:45,166 --> 00:21:48,708
[TSURUMI]
Iron. Iron.

390
00:21:48,791 --> 00:21:52,750
Edogai had an unusual obsession
with tannin.

391
00:21:52,833 --> 00:21:55,375
A tanning process that takes
a lot of extra effort,

392
00:21:55,458 --> 00:21:58,041
which very few people
would bother to use.

393
00:21:58,125 --> 00:22:01,166
He shared that tidbit with me
and no one else.

394
00:22:04,625 --> 00:22:06,791
[EDOGAI'S VOICE] Tsurumi,
when these gloves get wet,

395
00:22:06,875 --> 00:22:08,750
you need to be extra careful.

396
00:22:10,500 --> 00:22:12,208
If they happen to touch
a particular thing

397
00:22:12,291 --> 00:22:14,333
while they're wet,
they'll turn black.

398
00:22:16,625 --> 00:22:19,208
[TSURUMI] The tannin
gets absorbed into the water,

399
00:22:19,291 --> 00:22:21,666
then it reacts with the iron.

400
00:22:21,750 --> 00:22:23,750
Edogai's last words
were telling me

401
00:22:23,833 --> 00:22:26,541
how I could detect
the fakes amongst the others.

402
00:22:26,625 --> 00:22:28,333
He sacrificed his life

403
00:22:28,416 --> 00:22:31,458
to give me five beautiful
counterfeit skins.

404
00:22:31,541 --> 00:22:34,333
I won't let that sacrifice
go to waste.

405
00:24:06,791 --> 00:24:10,166
[NARRATOR] Next time,
"Let's Talk About the Past."

